observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Mayor, Municipal Planning and Development Officer and concerned Municipal Officials to:
a. Ensure that priority development projects to be funded out of the 20% Development Fund are well-planned and procurement-and-implementation-ready;
b. Implement the priority development projects programmed during the year as embodied in the approved AIP and ensure optimum utilization of the 20% Development Fund in compliance with the provisions of DBM-DOF-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 1 series of 2020. (CY 2022 AAR Observation No. 7)

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to direct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to:
Ensure that all checks released to claimants are reported in the Report of Checks issued;
Verify and monitor all receipts and check releases to ensure that all transactions are completely recorded in the appropriate time/period;
Strengthen internal control on the release of checks and ensure that DVs are returned by the payees/suppliers to avoid delays in the recording of transactions; and
Submit the original disbursement vouchers with complete supporting documents.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the concerned officials and employees and the BAC to:
1) Abide by the rules and regulations of RA 9184 for procurement activities;
2) Comply with the requirements stated in the Letter of Agreement regarding formulation of an internal policy supported by a Sangguniang Bayan Resolution promoting sustainability measures of the project, to include among others, 1) Benefit Sharing Agreement 2) Criteria in the selection of member-recipient 3) Creation of an internal monitoring, validation, and project activity documentation teams; 
3) Submit original payroll for Check No. 615735; and
4) Submit valid ID with signature of the recipients.
